&gt; hi, is there any easy way to remove a test from a suite? i am fooling 
&gt; around with cactus and some of the tests are not implemented yet.


If I read between the lines I can imagine that the only problem you may 
have is that a run failes and the error message is &quot;&quot;No tests found in 
...&quot; (if it&#39;s not the problem, please give more infos)

cause of this problem: classes that extend TestCase _must_ have at least 
one valid test method (public, void return, no arg and beginning with 
&quot;test&quot;).

Several solutions:

- create an empty dummy test method:
     public void testDummy () {}
- find the testsuite that includes this class and remove the 
addTestSuite(myFaultyClass.class) call
- modify JUnit to implement a soft-error handling: if an error message 
starts with &quot;xyz&quot;, consider this as a warning and not as an error (in 
TestResult).

   public void runProtected(final Test test, Protectable p) {
     try {
       p.protect();
     } catch (AssertionFailedError e) {
       if (e.getMessage().startsWith(&quot;No tests found in&quot;)) {
          System.out.println(&quot;warning &quot; + e.getMessage());
       } else {
         addFailure(test, e);
       }
     } catch (ThreadDeath e) { // don&#39;t catch ThreadDeath by accident
       throw e;
     } catch (Throwable e) {
       addError(test, e);
     }
   }

